# Linux Disk Management

## Commands Covered

- df
- du
- lsblk
- mount

---

## Purpose

Monitor storage usage and identify directories consuming disk space.

---

## Safe Cleanup

```bash
sudo apt clean
sudo apt autoclean
sudo apt autoremove
```

---

## Best Practices

- Check disk usage before deleting files.
- Remove only unnecessary data.
- Verify free space after cleanup.
